Observation Details: Manakins were initially unheard and virtually unseen for about the first 20 minutes I stood there.  Then I saw some movement, including one male sitting still, with some grooming behavior. I continued to stand still except for taking photos. Around 3:15 pm, coincident with sunlight penetrating to the ground, I began to see active bird movements. Then  2-3  males began vocalizing. Activity heightened. In my one minute video I hear various songs and see two males zipping from twig to twig while snapping wings. Behavior occurred in an area of about 5-6 feet wide and without apparent changes having been made to leaf litter.
